**![](data:image/png;base64,)**The action icons displayed at the top of the Flat File Reader's configuration page allow to perform global actions on the Flat file data structure.

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Import structure**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-reader-global-actions#importing-a-data-structure)

Define the structure to read Flat input files using an existing Flat file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download structure**

Download a copy of the data structure to your local filesystem in XML format (for example: *FFReader_structure.xml*).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Settings**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-reader-global-actions#configuring-the-flat-file-readers-general-settings)

Define the general settings of the Flat File Reader resource.

### Importing a data structure
This feature allows to define the structure to read Flat input files using an existing XML structure file, previously exported from another DT3 project using the **Download structure **command.

The functionality is useful, for example, if you want to import the structure of an existing Flat File Reader instead of manually defining the required fields.

> Note

It is always possible to modify the imported structure.

> Important

This action will permanently delete and overwrite the existing data structure.

- Open the Flat File Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Import structure**).

> Warning

If a data structure has already been defined for the Flat File Reader, the system notifies you that importing a new structure file will discard the existing data. Click **YES, CONTINUE **to proceed anyway.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click **YES, CONTINUE**.

- Select the required XML structure file from the file browser window that appears.

If the structure was imported correctly, the schema tree will be populated with all the records and structures defined in the imported file, overwriting any existing data; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Tip

When done, a notification message is displayed on the bottom-right to inform you of the result of the **Import structure **action.

### Configuring the Flat File Reader's general settings
- Open the XML Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Section**

**Parameter**

**Description**

**General**

**Name**

Name of the Flat File Reader

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the Flat File Reader

**Structure**

**Ignore unmapped rows**

Select this option to ignore unmapped rows.

**Schema**

**Schema name**

View and edit the name of the current data schema.

**Manage schemas**

Click on this link to manage the available data schema, as described in [Managing data schemas](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-reader-global-actions#managing-data-schemas) below.

> Tip

The **Applied to **section lists the Data Transformation components using this data schema, allowing you to evaluate the impacts of adding, deleting or modifying its elements.

#### Managing data schemas
- Click on the **Manage schemas **link to open the dedicated panel; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Move your mouse over the name of a data schema to display the context actions; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select one of the available actions:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download**

Download the data schema to your local filesystem.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Edit the name of the data schema.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently remove the data schema from the project.

> Important

This action cannot be undone.

If a data schema is currently used by one or more project components, this action is not available.

- If a data schema is used by one or more project components, a blue dot is displayed next to it. Click on it to see which resources are using the structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A detail panel listing the resources already using the selected structure is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

# 
> Tip

Click on the name of a resource to open it in its dedicated editor.

It is also possible to download or rename the data schema from this panel.
